## Privacy Notice

monVOX is designed with privacy as a core principle:

- No data collection or telemetry by default
- All AI processing can be performed on-device
- User data remains encrypted and local
- Open source for transparency and auditability

Users are responsible for:
- Configuring their own API keys for cloud AI services
- Understanding the privacy implications of their chosen AI providers
- Complying with applicable privacy laws and regulations

---

## Security Disclaimer

While monVOX implements security best practices including:
- Biometric authentication
- Encrypted local storage
- Comprehensive audit logging
- Secure coding practices

Users should:
- Keep their devices updated with latest security patches
- Use strong device passcodes in addition to biometric authentication
- Regularly review audit logs for suspicious activity
- Report security issues responsibly to project maintainers

The maintainers make no guarantees about the absolute security of this software and users assume responsibility for their own data protection.